1
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:39,041
[YOICHI grunts]
Why do I feel such icy dread?

2
00:00:39,125 --> 00:00:40,541
[OLMINU]
Huh?

3
00:00:40,625 --> 00:00:42,666
Something approaches.

4
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:45,750
The night air smells
of Sekigahara.

5
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,833
Of blood, waiting to be spilt!

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,875
[BLACK KING]
Find them. Hunt them down!

7
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:00,750
[JOAN OF ARC] En avant,
Gilles de Rais!

8
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:05,666
That righteous stench will lead
us straight to the Drifters!

9
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:06,958
[BLACK KING]
End them!

10
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:10,125
Cast them down
into the darkness!

11
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:12,833
Before these
branches bear fruit,

12
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:16,166
consign them to the flames.

13
00:01:21,375 --> 00:01:25,583
Hey, you hear that?
What is that sound?

14
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:31,208
[ELF A yells]

15
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:37,416
[JOAN OF ARC]
I have sussed them out.

16
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,041
Just like the Dauphin.

17
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:41,708
How they stink of righteousness.

18
00:01:41,791 --> 00:01:44,625
Drifters!

19
00:01:44,708 --> 00:01:46,666
[ELVES scream]

20
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,791
[JOAN OF ARC]
Show your faces, you cowards!

21
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:50,458
Come out and die!

22
00:01:50,541 --> 00:01:53,625
Let me burn your
sinful flesh to ash!

23
00:01:53,708 --> 00:01:56,500
[JOAN OF ARK laughs]

24
00:01:56,583 --> 00:01:58,958
[TOYOHISA] You seem very
proud of that trick.

25
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:02,208
It makes me wonder if
it's all you can do.

26
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:06,291
Perhaps you mean to kill
me with words. Is that it?

27
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,583
En garde!

28
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:43,333
[hooves pounding]

29
00:03:49,666 --> 00:03:52,750
Shara, rally all the
men without delay.

30
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,916
Make sure they've
plenty of arrows.

31
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,833
Have the women flee
into the forest.

32
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:58,875
Yes, sir.

33
00:03:58,958 --> 00:04:00,875
Time we bled their cavalry.

34
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:02,958
Are you sure that is wise?

35
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:05,083
Many years after your time,

36
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:08,250
my strategies were the doom
of many a mounted warrior,

37
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:10,916
my doubting young Yoichi. Heh!

38
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,875
I will leave you to it, then.

39
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:16,833
While you deal death
to a multitude...

40
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:22,208
...I fight a mountain.

41
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,916
Gilles de Rais, chop the
pretty one to kindling.

42
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,625
This Drifter has a
fierier fate in store.

43
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:40,416
Jeanne, fight with honor.

44
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,000
Felled the rampart...
with a blow!

45
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:59,000
Such strength in this man!
Just like Musashibo Benkei!

46
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,416
[JOAN OF ARC]
Hear me well!

47
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,458
You meddling Drifters
are all that hinders

48
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:04,208
the Black King's ambitions!

49
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:07,458
First we annihilate you,
then the rest of this world!

50
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:10,291
You're an End? The way
you were described to me,

51
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,458
I thought you'd cut a
more imposing figure,

52
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:13,666
though I must say,

53
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:16,291
you do seem as crazy
as I was led to believe.

54
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:17,750
Really, you're so
slight of frame,

55
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:20,000
I could mistake you for a woman.

56
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:22,750
[growls]

57
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:34,958
[TOYOHISA grunts]

58
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:37,500
Voila, you arrogant
little harlequin.

59
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:39,916
Trapped by my inferno, oui?

60
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
What now?

61
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:44,916
What the 'ell are you
going to do, you bastard?

62
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,666
If you're not going to answer,
you may as well die screaming!

63
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,708
[OLMINU shouts]

64
00:05:57,625 --> 00:05:59,833
What is this villainy?

65
00:05:59,916 --> 00:06:03,583
As an Octobrist, my solemn
duty is to defend the life

66
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:06,333
of a Drifter in any way I can!

67
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:08,625
[JOAN OF ARC grunts]

68
00:06:09,958 --> 00:06:13,166
[OLMINU yelps]

69
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,250
Well-played, Olmine!

70
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:23,291
I didn't know you
dealt in magic!

71
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:27,083
Well, truth be known, all I
can do is conjure those walls.

72
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:29,541
And only twice more, at that.

73
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,041
The Grand Master of our order

74
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,958
could've been of real
use to you right now.

75
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:36,208
As a magical neophyte,

76
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:40,250
I'm basically a millstone
around your neck.

77
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,666
Are you kidding?

78
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:44,250
You saved my life back there,
you know that, right?

79
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:45,291
[gasps]

80
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:46,958
[TOYOHISA]
You have my gratitude.

81
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:50,333
What? No! Don't bow to me!
I was just doing my job!

82
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,125
Look! The fire rages unchecked!

83
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:55,291
Save your thanks for a
time less fraught with woe!

84
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:57,125
[chuckles] Withholding
one's thanks

85
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,750
comes with its own dangers.

86
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:02,000
Who's to say we're not
a moment away from death?

87
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:04,750
[gasps]

88
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:07,916
That lunatic's hatred burns
hotter than a furnace,

89
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,500
but he's less of a threat than
he would have us believe.

90
00:07:10,583 --> 00:07:12,541
He has a weakness.

91
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:16,666
What? A weakness?
How would you know that?

92
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:23,083
[TOYOHISA] Intuition, born of
blood and battle. A hunch.

93
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:27,541
Look at his handiwork. Fire and
smoke as far as the eye can see.

94
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:31,083
But for all the carnage,
there's a desperation to it.

95
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,458
[TOYOHISA] Power, wielded by
a man once powerless.

96
00:07:35,541 --> 00:07:38,375
This is a soul with
something to prove.

97
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,000
I face a slave.

98
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:42,666
Chained to the trauma
that made him an End.

99
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,458
It makes him irrational.

100
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,916
Easy to slay.

101
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,416
[OLMINU]
I fear these feudal Drifters.

102
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,375
The smile he gives in gratitude

103
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:55,125
is the same he gives at the
thought of taking a head.

104
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:58,416
You said before you had two
charms left, isn't that so?

105
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,875
[OLMINU]
Um... right!

106
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:02,250
[TOYOHISA]
Excellent.

107
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,125
Do exactly as I instruct you.

108
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:08,458
And after that, run like
hell for the trees.

109
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:32,166
He's a monster!

110
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:36,000
That hulking spearman
is a beast of a fighter,

111
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,916
but Yoichi's matching
him at every turn!

112
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:42,416
[GILLES DE RAIS grunts]

113
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:46,125
[chuckles]

114
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:50,291
A foe like that and he laughs?

115
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,333
[laughs]

116
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,666
[YOSHITSUNE] Let it all out.
That's a good lad.

117
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:58,541
Take pleasure in the fight.

118
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,208
Showing one's
prowess to the world

119
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:02,291
is nothing to be ashamed of.

120
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,708
When it comes to death at
a distance, you are a master.

121
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:08,833
This beats shooting at
Taira war-fans, eh?

122
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:09,875
[GILLES DE RAIS grunts]

123
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,125
[YOICHI grunts]

124
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,875
[YOSHITSUNE] You've played
your hand to great effect,

125
00:09:23,958 --> 00:09:25,416
Gilles de Rais.

126
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:28,583
That should wipe the
smirk off his face.

127
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:30,250
[YOICHI]
So many arrows in him,

128
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,666
and most in spots
that would kill a man.

129
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:35,083
How does he yet live?

130
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:40,625
My quest is unfulfilled.

131
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:43,750
Thus, do I scorn
the reaper's call.

132
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,833
Ah... Truly! You sound...

133
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:49,125
[laughs] ...just like Benkei!

134
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:51,291
Ah, nostalgia!

135
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:03,541
All right, you.
Lend me a tapered ear.

136
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,583
I, the Demon King of
the Sixth Heaven,

137
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:09,458
will now teach you the basics
of slaughtering cavalry.

138
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:13,333
Oh yeah. Anyone who
fails the lesson, dies.

139
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:15,291
They might freeze the
blood at first glance,

140
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:18,083
but they're not as
lethal as you may think.

141
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:20,625
I understand if this
statement beggars belief.

142
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:21,875
It's a terrible sight,

143
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:25,000
your foe galloping
towards you, eyes ablaze.

144
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,541
But when that
bloodlust drives them

145
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:28,458
into a forest like this one.

146
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:32,583
bereft of any foot soldiers,
the tables are quick to turn.

147
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:35,208
The fools think they're
death incarnate.

148
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:39,583
And as soon as the safety of
the open field is behind them...

149
00:10:39,666 --> 00:10:41,000
...we strike.

150
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:43,500
Corralling them with
rope and bits of wood.

151
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:45,708
Rushing into the woods
is not their triumph,

152
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:46,958
but their undoing.

153
00:10:47,041 --> 00:10:50,250
A lesson I paid dearly
for in another life.

154
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:52,583
Now finish them off.

155
00:10:54,625 --> 00:10:58,166
[ENDS SOLDIERS grunting]

156
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:00,750
[NOBUNAGA] Fire from high
ground, and victory's yours.

157
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:01,916
Class dismissed!

158
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,875
I-In the blink of an eye...

159
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:05,833
...they're undone.

160
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:10,166
[NOBUNAGA]
This reminds me of Nagashino.

161
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:14,458
Highly-trained horsemen,
skewered by a storm of arrows.

162
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:16,958
The development of
firearms in this world

163
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:19,875
may propel them
into a new era of war.

164
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:22,625
That's why, no matter
what the cost,

165
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:27,083
we need to forge as many guns
as we have hands to fire them!

166
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:36,000
But the issue for now is that
we must kill these two Ends...

167
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:39,083
...before they burn
us to a crisp.

168
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:47,291
[JOAN OF ARC] Where are you?
We're not finished!

169
00:11:47,375 --> 00:11:50,416
Come out and face
your death, You coward!

170
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:53,833
There's no sanctuary
from my wrath!

171
00:11:56,875 --> 00:12:00,500
[JOAN OF ARC] If you deny me,
I will devour everything,

172
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:02,708
forest and castle alike!

173
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:04,416
[TOYOHISA]
You will do no such thing.

174
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,458
[JOAN OF ARC grunts]

175
00:12:07,125 --> 00:12:10,625
[TOYOHISA] The castle is
a ruin, but it's our ruin!

176
00:12:15,208 --> 00:12:16,791
There you are.

177
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:18,666
I'm ready. But are you?

178
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:21,500
[whimpers]

179
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:33,750
This time there is no escaping.

180
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:36,416
[TOYOHISA]
Agreed. For you, at least.

181
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,000
[OLMINU grunts]

182
00:12:38,083 --> 00:12:40,791
[JOAN OF ARC]
Know that you die a fool.

183
00:12:55,666 --> 00:12:59,875
[JOAN OF ARC] A wall?
At your back? Are you insane?

184
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:01,208
Indeed.

185
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:05,041
We warriors of Satsuma are
feared for our insanity.

186
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:09,375
[grunts]

187
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:14,291
[TOYOHISA]
Now. Bid farewell to your head!

188
00:13:14,375 --> 00:13:16,125
[JOAN OF ARC]
He fears me not! But why?

189
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:18,000
A wall to his back. Death ahead.

190
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:21,750
And yet, he glares at me,
defiant, blade in his teeth!

191
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:24,208
Go! Do it, Olmine!

192
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:27,333
All right! But this is madness!

193
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,500
[TOYOHISA yells]

194
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:37,416
No! Why? This should
not be possible!

195
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,208
[OLMINU] When I told him
of my wall-summoning charm,

196
00:13:39,291 --> 00:13:40,875
I never dreamed he bid me use it

197
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:43,375
to launch him towards
that demonic creature!

198
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:45,333
Who does that?

199
00:13:45,416 --> 00:13:46,458
The Grand Master
warned me that

200
00:13:46,541 --> 00:13:49,375
warriors of the Sengoku
era were brutal.

201
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:53,541
But him, this Toyohisa,
death is his canvas.

202
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:56,458
If it meant one more chance to
strike a head from its neck.

203
00:13:56,541 --> 00:14:00,208
he would lay down his life
in the blink of an eye!

204
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:03,458
Isn't that behavior what
we fear from the Ends?

205
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:05,291
[TOYOHISA]
Even with this castle in ruins,

206
00:14:05,375 --> 00:14:08,208
it boasts a feature that's
about to be of use to me!

207
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:09,416
[gasps]

208
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,916
[JOAN OF ARC]
The well!

209
00:14:15,291 --> 00:14:19,875
[JOAN OF ARC]
This... This is water!

210
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:24,416
How I did long for this.
For its cooling embrace!

211
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:27,583
When the flames took me!

212
00:14:29,958 --> 00:14:34,875
[JOAN OF ARC]
Water!

213
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:38,916
Burn, witch! And let your
suffering be like unto music

214
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,333
to the Lord our God!

215
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:43,375
[laughs] You dressed like
a man on the battlefield,

216
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:45,250
but now you scream
like the whore you are!

217
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,708
Behold! The fire eats
away at her clothing!

218
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:50,250
We'll finally see what she's
hiding away down there!

219
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:52,708
[PEASANT] Come, thou harlot
of Orleans! Show us more!

220
00:14:52,791 --> 00:14:57,000
Just pretend we're your
damnable Charles! Ha!

221
00:14:57,083 --> 00:15:04,125
[JOAN OF ARC] Witch. Harlot.
All I did was fight for France.

222
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:07,791
Merciful God, how come
I to such an end?

223
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:13,333
[JOAN OF ARC gasps]

224
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,541
[JOAN OF ARC gasps]

225
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:33,791
Join us. We, who were
cast aside.

226
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:36,875
[grunts]

227
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:41,416
[TOYOHISA]
Huh?

228
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:46,666
What the hell is this?
You're not a man at all!

229
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,666
[gasps]

230
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,375
Just because you're
wearing armor,

231
00:15:50,458 --> 00:15:53,000
doesn't mean you
belong on a battlefield!

232
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,541
Taking your head
brings me only shame!

233
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:58,166
Begone! War is a man's work!

234
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,083
[gasps]

235
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:01,583
Imbecile.

236
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:03,875
You know not of what you speak.

237
00:16:03,958 --> 00:16:06,375
We fought for the
people of France.

238
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:09,416
The down-trodden
children of Christ.

239
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:13,083
How we bled and burned for them!

240
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:14,875
That was my work!

241
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:15,916
[TOYOHISA grunts]

242
00:16:24,375 --> 00:16:25,791
[TOYOHISA]
Shut up!

243
00:16:25,875 --> 00:16:29,250
I've never heard of France,
so why should I give a damn?

244
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,541
The same goes for
this "Christ" person!

245
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:34,333
The fate of his children
is none of my concern!

246
00:16:34,416 --> 00:16:37,666
All you <i>gaijin</i> spout such
a river of nonsense!

247
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:39,750
Now, I'm going to
leave this well

248
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:44,500
and slay that towering spearman
you rode into battle with.

249
00:16:44,583 --> 00:16:49,083
If I die tonight, it'll be
the work of a man!

250
00:17:26,125 --> 00:17:27,166
[gasps]

251
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:30,750
Impossible! Why won't he die?

252
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:40,083
[YOICHI]
Yes. Now fall!

253
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:45,541
[gasps]

254
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,291
[YOICHI groans]

255
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,000
Dammit, no!

256
00:17:57,083 --> 00:17:59,000
Men, he's killing Yoichi!

257
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:01,208
Hit him with every
arrow you've got!

258
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:08,208
[SHARA]
It's as though he's immortal!

259
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:11,583
Forget all that.
Whoever lives must die!

260
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:14,333
Some bastards just make
you work harder for it!

261
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:18,166
Now shoot him! Shoot him!

262
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,875
[YOSHITSUNE] Goodness!
The Benkei comparison was apt!

263
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:40,791
What in tarnation
are we ridin' into?

264
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:42,500
Damned if I know!

265
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,375
[NOBUNAGA]
Who are they?

266
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:49,583
You are a stain upon this world!

267
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:57,750
You are wrath incarnate.

268
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:01,291
Hate made flesh!
Living contempt!

269
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:08,791
[KID]
One last hurrah!

270
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:11,375
Go down, you som'bitch!

271
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:19,833
[BOTH gasp]

272
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:36,208
[dragon roars]

273
00:19:36,291 --> 00:19:39,666
[speaking Orte]


274
00:20:05,541 --> 00:20:07,333
He's still alive?

275
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:11,458
Whuh? Naw! What manner
o' devilment is this?

276
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:32,541
[chuckles]

277
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:34,958
[GILLES DE RAIS]
They burned La Pucelle

278
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:38,250
at the stake as
a heretic, a witch.

279
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:40,166
And now I fear the
gates of Paradise

280
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:42,541
have been barred to her.

281
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:46,250
I will follow you, Jeanne,
even into Hell.

282
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:50,958
I will commit such villainies
as to damn my immortal soul.

283
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:55,416
Know that I am
on my way, milady.

284
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,333
Jeanne was not
consigned to Hell.

285
00:20:58,416 --> 00:21:03,500
But when I found her here...
she was not the same.

286
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:05,375
Her heart was dark.

287
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:08,916
Hell awaits her this time,
which is why I must go there

288
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,833
ahead of her and
prepare the way.

289
00:21:11,916 --> 00:21:14,750
For Jeanne, now and ever.

290
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:29,291
As I thought. His body
transformed into salt.

291
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:33,875
What just...?
What just happened?

292
00:21:37,208 --> 00:21:40,000
Grand Master, over here!

293
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:44,041
Kudos to you, Olmine.
You've done excellent work.

294
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:47,083
Sir! It was my duty,
nothing more!

295
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:49,333
[NOBUNAGA]
How do you fit into all this?

296
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:51,916
Clearly, you're involved.

297
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,958
I'm just a man.
A man who hates the Ends.

298
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:58,083
I'm the leader of the
Octobrist Organization,

299
00:21:58,166 --> 00:22:01,291
to which Olmine has
pledged her allegiance.

300
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:05,208
Giving aid to the Drifters
ranks as first among my duties.

301
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:07,916
And the best way I
can lend them that aid,

302
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,375
is to destroy every
End I encounter.

303
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:17,208
I believe you're a
Drifter your own self.

304
00:22:17,291 --> 00:22:19,250
What's your name?

305
00:22:20,708 --> 00:22:23,708
Abe no Haruakira.

306
00:23:56,541 --> 00:24:01,500
[SOUND VOICE chants]

